10. Magic Methods in PHP
Ans:
The function names __construct(), __destruct(), __call(), __callStatic(), __get(), __set(), __isset(), __unset(), __sleep(), __wakeup(), __toString(), __invoke(), __set_state(), __clone() and __debugInfo() are magical in PHP classes.

Remove all HTML tags from a string:
filter_var($str, FILTER_SANITIZE_STRING);

FILTER_SANITIZE_EMAIL
FILTER_SANITIZE_URL

===============
The FILTER_SANITIZE_NUMBER_INT filter removes all illegal characters from a number.
This filter allows digits and . + -
FILTER_SANITIZE_NUMBER_INT
===============

FILTER_FLAG_STRIP_LOW - Remove characters with ASCII value < 32
filter_var( $string , FILTER_SANITIZE_STRING, FILTER_FLAG_STRIP_LOW);

======================

The FILTER_SANITIZE_URL filter removes all illegal URL characters from a string.
This filter allows all letters, digits and $-_.+!*'(),{}|\\^~[]`"><#%;/?:@&=

======================
TO SET NO CACHE FOR HTML FILE

		  	header("Expires: Mon, 26 Jul 1990 05:00:00 GMT");
			header("Last-Modified: " . gmdate("D, d M Y H:i:s") . " GMT");
			header("Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate");
			header("Cache-Control: post-check=0, pre-check=0", false);
			header("Pragma: no-cache");
      
